<br /><span id="goog_1451176197"></span><span id="goog_1451176198"></span>There are some climbing frames in the middle of Peron right next to the Marie. Some leafy trees give shade to some benches and some very low branching trees are good for climbing.<br /><br />There's a tiny train as well, it's a log with a chimney on top but it does the job.<br /><br />About 20m away there is a small <a href="http://maps.google.fr/places/fr/p%C3%A9ron/place-saint-antoine/39/-auberge-communale-la-fruitiere?hl=en&amp;gl=fr">cafe</a> which is sometimes open.<br /><br /><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="tr-caption-container" style="float: right; margin-left: 1em; text-align: right;"><tbody><tr><td style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TIz_giF2SNI/AAAAAAAAzWE/WeQmGUofbIE/s1600/IMAG1069.jpg" imageanchor="1" style="clear: right; margin-bottom: 1em; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;"><img border="0" height="218" src="http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_o22J03lZ9Gw/TIz_giF2SNI/AAAAAAAAzWE/WeQmGUofbIE/s320/IMAG1069.jpg" width="320" /></a></td></tr><tr><td class="tr-caption" style="text-align: center;">Peron octagon and a tiny train.</td></tr></tbody></table>

